\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {(12)\tab Q. How do I turn off the movies that play when I start Midtown Madness?
\par }{\b0 
\par }\pard\plain \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \f2\fs20\cgrid {\b\f15 A.}{\f15 \tab You have several options if you don't want to watch the movies that play when you start Midtown Madness. First, you can hold down the 
left mouse button (or press ESC) to skip the movies when you start the game. To permanently disable them, you can either delete or rename the AVI files (located in the folder where you installed Midtown Madness) or run the No Movie shortcut (also located 
in the folder where you installed Midtown Madness).
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\b\f15 
\par }\pard \s17\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f15 
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f15 (13)\tab Q. Is there a list of game controls I can access while playing Midtown Madness?
\par }{\f15 
\par }{\b\f15 A.}{\f15 \tab Yes. While you are racing (or cruising), press F1 to pause the game and display a complete list of game controls. Press ESC or (click the Exit Menu button) when you are ready to get back in the action.\line \line 
You can also consult the list of game controls included in the Midtown Madness jewel case booklet.
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b\f15 (14)\tab Q. I want to customize the control assignments for my joystic
k (or other game controller). Which actions/inputs can I assign to which controls?
\par 
\par A.\tab }{\f15 Steering and driving inputs (i.e., turning left and right, accelerating and braking) can be assigned to either control axes or buttons or keys. Other controls can only b
e assigned to buttons or keys (i.e., Map and HUD toggles, Shift Up and Shift Down, Change Views, etc.).\line \line 
To customize your controller assignments, click the Options button (located in the upper right corner of any game screen), and then click Control Optio
ns. In the Key Functions list, click the name of the function you want to assign to a new control or key, and then press the control or key you want. To revert to the default settings, click the Defaults button at the bottom of the Control Options screen.

\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \f2\fs20\cgrid {\b\f15 
\par (15)\tab Q. Is there anything I can do to improve my cornering at high speeds?
\par }{\f15 
\par }{\b\f15 A.}{\f15 \tab When cornering at high speeds, try using the handbrake and accelerator at the same time. Braking alone can slow you down too much, while accelerating through a corner without 
braking can slide you right into traffic. To use the handbrake, press the SPACEBAR (if the keyboard is your selected controller) or joystick button 2 (if the joystick is your selected controller).
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \s23\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {(16)\tab Q. What do the Midtown Safe Mode, No Sound, No Movie, and Redetect Video shortcuts in my Midtown Madness folder do?
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
\par }{\b\f15 A.\tab }{\f15 The Midtown Safe Mode, No Sound, and No Movie, and Redetect Video shortcuts are included to help you solve video card, audio, and video problems you may encounter when installing or playing Midtown Madness.\line \line 
Use the Midtown Safe Mode shortcut if you encounter problems with your video card configuration. When you use this shortcut, Midtown Madness starts with the Rendering option set to Software
 Only and the opening movies are not played. Midtown Madness also automatically redetects your video card. You can confirm that your video card is recognized by Midtown Madness by checking the Renderer list in Graphic Options (Options menu).\line \line 
Use the Redetect Video shortcut when you've changed video cards. When you use this shortcut, Midtown Madness will recognize your new video card and set Graphics options (Options menu) accordingly. (See also Question #23).\line \line 
Use the No Sound shortcut to start Midtown Mad
ness with all audio, including audio effects, music, and in-game commentary, turned off. Use this shortcut if you're having problems with sound in the game, or if you prefer a silent gameplay experience. You can turn these sounds back on in Audio Options 
(Options menu).\line \line 
Use the No Movie shortcut to start Midtown Madness without playing the opening movies. Use this shortcut if you're having problems with the movies that play when you start Midtown Madness, or if you don't want to see the movies each time yo
u start the game.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \f2\fs20\cgrid {\b\f15 
\par }\pard \s17\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f15 (17)\tab Q. How can I unlock locked vehicles?
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }{\b\f15 A.}{\f15 \tab To unlock specific vehicles, follow these steps:
\par }\pard \s17\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }{\b\f15 City Bus:}{\f15  To unlock the City Bus, Amateurs must finish in first, second, or third in any two races. Professionals need to take first place in any two races.
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 \tab 
\par }\pard \s17\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f15 Freightliner Century Class 18-wheel truck:}{\f15  To unlock the Freightliner, Amateurs and Professionals must "beat the clock" in any five Blitz races.
\par }\pard \s17\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par \tab }{\b\f15 '68 Ford Mustang Fastback: }{\f15 To unlock the Fastback, Amateurs must finish in the\line top three places in any five Circuit races. Professionals must finish in first place in any five Circuit races.
\par 
\par \tab }{\b\f15 Mustang Police Car:}{\f15  To unlock the Police Car, Amateurs must finish in the top three places in any six Checkpoint races. Professionals must finish in first place.
\par \tab 
\par }\pard \s17\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f15 Panoz GTR:}{\f15 
 The only way to unlock the awesome power of the Panoz GTR is to accumulate 8,000 points while racing as a Professional (you don't earn points when you're racing as an Amateur!). Points are awarded based on two important criteria: how 
well you place in races, and which vehicles you're driving. If you finish well in a race driving a slower vehicle, you'll get more points than if you do the same thing in a\line faster car. 
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {(18)\tab Q. How can I play Midtown Madness with other people for free on the MSN Gaming Zone?
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
