\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {(19)\tab Q. I prefer more arcade-style racing games. How can I make Midtown Madness feel more like an arcade racer?
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
\par }{\b\f15 A.}{\f15 \tab 
By adjusting the Physics Realism setting, you can make Midtown Madness behave more like an arcade-style racing game. The Physics Realism slider is located on the Vehicles Screen, and you can assign a distinct Physics Realism setting to each vehicle feat
ured in Midtown Madness. To decrease the setting and make Midtown Madness behave more like an arcade racer, click the minus sign on the Physics Realism slider control.
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {(20)\tab Q. Sometimes I can customize race conditions (i.e., weather, time-of-day, pedestrian, cop, and traffic densities), and sometimes I can't. How come?
\par }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f15 A.}{\f15 \tab 
If you're racing as an Amateur, placing in the top three places in any one Circuit, Blitz, or Checkpoint race unlocks the weather, time-of-day, and traffic, pedestrian and cop density c
onditions for that specific race. This allows you to customize your race experience for new challenges (and new landspeed records!). If you're racing as a Professional, you'll have to place first in each Circuit, Blitz, or Checkpoint race for the same cus
tomization privileges.
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {(21)\tab Q. Why don't all my opponents follow the same path during a race? Am I missing something?
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {A.\tab }{\b0 Your opponents are exploiting every advantage they can find to fly across the finish line in front of you! They're cutting corners, u
sing shortcuts, diving into tunnels, driving on the sidewalk\emdash whatever it takes to win!\line \line 
Also keep in mind that in checkpoint races, you can clear the checkpoints in any order, so one of your opponents may have discovered a faster route that lets him or her
 charge through checkpoints in a more efficient manner. Following your opponents can be a smart strategy\emdash they can help you find new ways to win!\line \line 
To help you discover new routes, you can change which checkpoint the green checkpoint arrow is pointing at by pressing S to point toward the next checkpoint, and X to point toward the previous checkpoint.
\par }\pard \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\b0 
\par }\pard \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b0 
\par }{(22)\tab Q. I've run some races several times, but I still can't beat them. What can I do to improve my performance?
\par }{\b0 
\par }{A.}{\b0 \tab See Question #21 for tips on finding the best route for a specific race. Following your opponents can be a valuable learning experience!\line \line 
It's also important to take advantage of shortcuts and tunnels, and choosing the right vehicle for the job can make all the difference in the world. Sometimes y
ou need the pure power of the Ford F-350, while at other times you need the nimble handling of the new Ford Mustang GT. Most importantly, always remember: practice makes perfect!
\par }\pard \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\b0 
\par }\pard \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b0 
\par }{(23)\tab Q. How can I find out more about the vehicles featured in Midtown Madness?
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
\par }{\b\f15 A.\tab }{\f15 The Vehicles Showcase button on the Vehicles screen is your ticket to real-world information about the awesome vehicles featured in Midtown Madness.\line \line 
For the inside scoop on a specific vehicle, including real-world specifications and a URL for the
 manufacturer's World Wide Web site, click the vehicle's name in the Vehicles list on the Vehicles screen, and then click Vehicles Showcase. When you're ready to return to the Vehicles screen, click Done.
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {(24)\tab Q. I want to drive using manual transmission. How do I shift once I'm in the game?
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\f15 
\par }\pard\plain \s18\fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f15\fs20\cgrid {A.}{\b0 \tab 
To drive using manual transmission, you can either clear the Automatic Transmission check box on the Vehicles screen, or press T while you're racing to toggle between automatic and manual transmissions.\line \line 
To upshift while you are racing, press A. To downshift, press Z.
\par }\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \fs20\cgrid {
